<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>TraceWorks™ | Public-Record Investigative Reports</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles.css" />
    <!-- Progressive Web App manifest -->
    <link rel="manifest" href="/manifest.json" />
    <meta name="theme-color" content="#ffffff" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <main class="container homepage-v2">
      <header class="topbar">
        <div>
          <p class="topbar-kicker">PUBLIC-RECORD INVESTIGATIVE INTELLIGENCE</p>
          <h1>Trace<span>Works™</span></h1>
        </div>
        <nav class="top-links" aria-label="Primary">
          <a href="#packages">Packages</a>
          <a href="#how-it-works">How it works</a>
          <a href="#secure-intake">Secure intake</a>
          <a href="/launch-readiness.html">Launch readiness</a>
          <a class="gold-btn" href="#secure-intake">Start request</a>
        </nav>
      </header>

      <section class="hero structure-hero">
        <p class="kicker">Built for attorneys, legal ops, and investigators</p>
        <h2>Evidence-logged public-record reports for legal workflows.</h2>
        <p class="hero-sub">TraceWorks runs configurable county/state public-record research, logs exactly what was queried, and delivers structured reports with confidence labels and manual-review flags.</p>
        <div class="hero-cta">
          <a class="gold-btn" href="#packages">View packages</a>
          <a class="ghost-btn" href="#secure-intake">Secure intake</a>
        </div>
        <p class="hero-proof">Confidential handling • Public-record based • Fast turnaround • Non-legal-opinion reporting</p>
      </section>

      <section class="trust-row" aria-label="Trust signals">
        <article><h4>Public-record based</h4><p>Configured county/state sources with evidence timestamps.</p></article>
        <article><h4>Evidence logged</h4><p>Each query URL + parameters + retrieval status are retained.</p></article>
        <article><h4>Confidential delivery</h4><p>Secure intake and controlled report distribution workflow.</p></article>
        <article><h4>Fast output</h4><p>Automated execution with explicit gaps and fallback pathways.</p></article>
      </section>

      <section id="packages" class="section-head">
        <div>
          <p class="kicker">Package selection</p>
          <h3>Choose the business-facing report package</h3>
          <p>Primary packages for legal operations; heir/probate appears in its own section below due to separate intent.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="cards" id="packageCards"></section>

      <section class="heir-focus">
        <h3>Heir / Probate Research</h3>
        <p>Use this when the objective is heir candidate research, probate indicators, and lawful verification sequencing (not legal adjudication of heirship).</p>
        <div class="cards heir-cards" id="heirPackageCards"></div>
      </section>

      <dialog id="packageModal" class="package-modal">
        <article class="package-modal-content">
          <button type="button" class="package-modal-close" id="packageModalClose" aria-label="Close package details">×</button>
          <p class="label" id="modalPackageLabel"></p>
          <h3 id="modalPackageTitle"></h3>
          <p class="price" id="modalPackagePrice"></p>
          <p id="modalPackageSummary"></p>
          <h4>What your report includes</h4>
          <ul id="modalPackageIncludes"></ul>
          <div class="package-modal-actions">
            <a id="modalReportPreview" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Preview report sample</a>
            <button type="button" id="modalSelectPackage">Select This Package</button>
          </div>
        </article>
      </dialog>

      <section id="how-it-works" class="process">
        <h3>How it works</h3>
        <ol>
          <li><strong>Submit request:</strong> provide subject/property context and case purpose.</li>
          <li><strong>Research engine runs:</strong> configured public-record + web intelligence workflows execute.</li>
          <li><strong>Report generated:</strong> findings, evidence appendix, and gaps are assembled.</li>
          <li><strong>Report delivered:</strong> artifacts are stored and delivery email is sent.</li>
        </ol>
      </section>

      <section class="form-wrap intake-shell" id="secure-intake">
        <div class="section-head intake-head">
          <div>
            <p class="kicker">Secure intake</p>
            <h3>Submit case intake</h3>
            <p>Grouped for legal operations: subject/property info, requester info, case purpose, and compliance confirmation.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <form id="checkoutForm">
          <fieldset>
            <legend>Subject / property info</legend>
            <label>Selected Package<input id="packageId" name="packageId" readonly required /></label>
            <label>Subject Name / Entity<input name="companyName" required /></label>
            <label>Known Website / Profile<input name="website" placeholder="https://..." /></label>
          </fieldset>

          <fieldset>
            <legend>Requester info</legend>
            <label>Your Name<input name="customerName" required /></label>
            <label>Email<input name="customerEmail" type="email" required /></label>
          </fieldset>

          <fieldset>
            <legend>Case purpose</legend>
            <label>Case Objective<textarea name="goals" rows="4" placeholder="Service, title chain review, probate research, contact verification, etc."></textarea></label>
          </fieldset>

          <fieldset>
            <legend>Compliance confirmation</legend>
            <label class="checkbox"><input type="checkbox" name="legalConsent" required /> I confirm lawful-use and authorization requirements.</label>
            <label class="checkbox"><input type="checkbox" name="tosConsent" required /> I accept Terms and service limitations.</label>
          </fieldset>

          <button type="submit">Continue to Secure Checkout</button>
          <p id="status" class="status"></p>
        </form>
      </section>

      <section class="faq-block" id="faq">
        <h3>FAQ</h3>
        <details><summary>What’s included?</summary><p>Configured source queries, evidence appendix, report sections, and gap disclosures.</p></details>
        <details><summary>What’s not included?</summary><p>No legal title opinion, no legal heir adjudication, and no legal advice.</p></details>
        <details><summary>Turnaround</summary><p>Most requests deliver same-day to 24h depending on source availability.</p></details>
        <details><summary>Disclaimers</summary><p>Reports are investigative outputs from accessible sources and may require manual validation.</p></details>
      </section>

      <section class="sales card">
        <h3>Request Enterprise Call</h3>
        <p>Running volume for a law firm, process network, or investigative team? Ask about account-level workflows.</p>
        <form id="salesForm">
          <label>Full Name<input name="name" required /></label>
          <label>Work Email<input name="email" type="email" required /></label>
          <label>Company<input name="company" required /></label>
          <label>Website<input name="website" placeholder="https://" /></label>
          <label>Monthly Cases<input name="monthlyCases" required /></label>
          <label>Budget Range<input name="budget" /></label>
          <label>Notes<textarea name="message" rows="3"></textarea></label>
          <button type="submit">Request Enterprise Call</button>
        </form>
        <p id="salesStatus" class="status"></p>
      </section>

      <footer class="footer">
        <p>© <span id="year"></span> TraceWorks™</p>
        <nav>
          <a href="/terms.html">Terms</a>
          <a href="/privacy.html">Privacy</a>
          <a href="/refund-policy.html">Refund Policy</a>
          <a href="/launch-readiness.html">Launch readiness</a>
        </nav>
      </footer>
    </main>

    <script type="module" src="/app.js"></script>
    <script>document.getElementById('year').textContent = new Date().getFullYear();</script>
  </body>
</html>
